I partnered with @ivorysoap to create an Ivory Care Pack for my Lola ❤️ with cozy items like a plush blanket and socks PLUS Ivory Gentle Moisturizing Body Wash and Gentle Deodorant made with pure ingredients.
 

Ivory Acts of Gentle Kindness initiative has allowed me to show my kids the importance of being kind to one another, especially the grandmas and the grandpas who have been lonely and isolated during the pandemic. Make a gentle care pack and tag @ivorysoap and use #IvoryKindness to continue to spread the word (and joy)! After all, the holidays are coming and we want to end up on the nice list 😉

Today is #WorldKindnessDay and I could not be more excited to partner with @ivorysoap to spread a little kindness across generations! This year has been really tough with the pandemic and our senior friends and family members have been the most isolated. Samuel and I made Ivory gentle care packs filled with amazing goodies like Ivory Gentle Moisturizing Body Wash and Gentle Deodorant, made with pure ingredients and designed for even the most sensitive skin, plus cozy items like fuzzy socks and blankets.

node.text: Every time I sing this song and listen to the lyrics, I cry. I cry because I’m so grateful for my children and I am so blessed that I get to kiss each of them everyday. I cherish every moment that I’m given with them and this song will forever be a part of our lives. As a kid I remember moms always crying and thinking they were crazy and weird and now I’m that weird and crazy lady times a million. Happy tears. I hope you love this @mamasingmysong keepsake song as much as we do.

node.text: I captured a truly special moment. Sean doesn’t have any brothers. I don’t have any brothers. We thought when we had Isaiah that these two boys would have such a great bond and one that we hadn’t personally experienced before. (We both have sisters, it’s different 🤣) Over the past three years we have witnessed a lot of fights, kisses, crying, laughing between the two of them and this video validated Sean’s and my hope for them. Here’s to raising brothers - all the chaos that it entails and these treasured moments sprinkled in ❤️
